title: For Sale/Trade:  Open Bolt RPB SAP
postcontent: 615-5five7-44three5Pretty cool peice of history here: I have a very early RPB Industries MAC 10 style gun from 1979 chambered in .45 ACP.This is the notorious semi auto open bolt that was reclassified as a machine gun by the BATF in a ruling in 1982. The ATF were confiscating them by the hundreds in Miami from narcos who converted them to full auto for use in the Miami drug wars against law enforcement and rival gangs. THIS IS A SEMI AUTO PISTOL. Not an MG. The ATF said that the ones in circulation are grandfathered in, however, any new ones produced in the same design are considered to be machine guns. So there will never be anymore than the ones out there already. These guns were produced for only three years so they are getting really hard to find. It utilizes U.S. Grease Gun magazines which are in plentiful supply. (around 10$)RPB SAP in .45 ACP.Original vented barrel shroud.Four 30 round magazines.
